Distribution in the Balkans. Albania
: 4km S of Vlorё, Llogorasё Pass, Vlorё District, above Prenjas, Librazhd District, between Hotolisht and Librazhd, 13km N of Ersekё, Leskovik District, Komnik (= Kamenice), Korçё District (
Mauriès et al. 1997
);
Bulgaria
: Stara Planina Mts., Central Balkan National Park, Rhodopes Mts.: Asenova Fortress, Kardzhali, Asenovgrad, Slashten, Hadzhidimovo; Rila Mts.: near Pastra, Rila National Park, Rila Monastery Natural Park; Melnik, Sveti Iliya Hill near Kalimantsi, Konyavska Planina Mt., near Haskovo, Mesta Valley, Momina Klisura Gorge, Dolna Koznitsa, Sandanski, Strumyani, P. Yavorov Railway Station (
Vagalinski & Stoev 2007
);
Greece
: Central Greece , near Anomusinitza ( type locality), Chalkidiki, west shore of the Volvi Lake, Petralona, Agia Anastasia Monastery, Asprovalta, Chalkidiki, Rentina outflow by Stavros, valley of Piniós by Tsagesi, Vermio Mt. in Kavala, West Macedonia , Olympos, Epirus, Ioannina, Karias, Elati, Tristenon, Ligiades, Konitsa, Aristi, Anemorachi, Votonosson, Katara , East Macedonia and Thrace, Rentina, around Alexandroupolis–Makri, Central Greece , Epirus, Pindos, Thessalia ( Strasser 1974 , 1976 );
Republic of Macedonia
: Golem Grad, near Prespa, Dojran Lake, Karadojranski Potok, Šar Planina Mt., Ljuboten, Treska, Vodno, near, Skopje (
